"{\"uid\": \"rvasia.org-asian-news-drag-queens-admit-paris-olympic-games-performance-parody-last-supper\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The artists involved in the opening ceremony of the 2024 Olympic Games have disclosed that their performance was, in fact,a parody of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 134, \"end\": 151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5802574483457463e-17, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The admission was made in online social media posts and statements to the media.\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking to the French media, Piche, a drag queen and rapper, said the performance was a tableau of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 272, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9997834172451977, \"rank\": 0.00021446814551114203, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The worldwide backlash showed that \\\"we have succeeded and we have done what had to be done, that we have been fair and representative,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Art always divides,\\\" Piche said.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As long as it does not move people, it's not art for me.\\\"\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But he insisted the parody of the Last Supper \\\"is not a provocation\\\" and justified it by saying \\\"it's a biblical representation that has been reused in pop culture for decades and it's never really been a problem.\\\"\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Piche denied any intention to provoke Christians and that there was nothing offensive in the show.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 868, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9625521607396281, \"rank\": 0.03887884249533134, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There were no real provocations or anything that was truly obscene,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We did not make fun of the painting at all\\u2026it's really just because it's queers and drag queens who use that representation that it bothers.\\\"\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also, Barbara Butch, an artist who portrayed Christ in performance, posted on Instagram a screenshot image of the presentation over an image of the Last Supper with the comment, \\\" Oh yes!\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1159, \"end\": 1172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 1231, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1285766118094213e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh yes!\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new gay testament!\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the post was deleted following the protests by Chriatians from across the globe.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On her Instagram profile, Butch says he is \\\"a Love activist, Dj and producer based in Paris.\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1285766118094213e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}, {\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999948568075, \"rank\": 5.143381553159012e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My aim is to unite people, gather humans & share love through music for all of Us to dance & make our hearts beat (in unison)!\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Music sounds better with all of Us!\\\"\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But their performance at the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games in Paris prompted massive division and sparked debates worldwide.\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999948568075, \"rank\": 5.143381553159012e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The drag queens admitted they deliberately parodied the Last Supper, countering the statements of the Olympic Games officials that there were not intentions to offend the Christians.\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 2033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2022, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9625521607396281, \"rank\": 0.03887884249533134, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the performance did offend not only ordinary Christians and religious heads, but also world leaders.\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2084, \"end\": 2094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9625521607396281, \"rank\": 0.03887884249533134, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mike Johnson, Speaker of the United States House of Representatives posted on X on July 28.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Last night's mockery of the Last Supper was shocking and insulting to Christian people around the world who watched the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9973222993919596, \"rank\": 0.002684794933368569, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The war on our faith and traditional values knows no bounds today.\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we know that truth and virtue will always prevail.\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Italian Deputy Prime Minister Matteo Salvini in a post wrote, \\\"Opening the Olympics by insulting billions of Christians around the world was a really bad start, dear French.\\\"\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2592, \"end\": 2599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.999998035466089, \"rank\": 1.009872653539272e-06, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2622, \"end\": 2636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Salvini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Salvini\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Salvini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Salvini\"}, {\"begin\": 2701, \"end\": 2711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9625521607396281, \"rank\": 0.03887884249533134, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2758, \"end\": 2764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9997834172451977, \"rank\": 0.00021446814551114203, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French bishops issued a statement on July 27 decrying the performance.\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2772, \"end\": 2778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9997834172451977, \"rank\": 0.00021446814551114203, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christian churches from across the globe expressed their solidarity with the Church in France in denouncing the Last Supper parody as a disrespect to the Christian faith.\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2843, \"end\": 2852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9973222993919596, \"rank\": 0.002684794933368569, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9805840638310284, \"rank\": 0.013906405763085708, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2997, \"end\": 3006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9973222993919596, \"rank\": 0.002684794933368569, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Radio Veritas Asia (RVA), a media platform of the Catholic Church, aims to share Christ.\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3015, \"end\": 3033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Veritas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Radio Veritas Asia\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Veritas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_Veritas\"}, {\"begin\": 3065, \"end\": 3080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999887308584365, \"rank\": 1.1255347834080342e-05, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RVA started in 1969 as a continental Catholic radio station to serve Asian countries in their respective local language, thus earning the tag 